entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: An open-source framework for agent technology. It positions itself as a platform without direct token integration, while planning revenue generation through cloud services and API wrapping.

entities.name: AI16Z
entities.description: A token planned as the settlement currency for the Agent-to-Agent (A2A) Marketplace within the ElizaOS ecosystem. Its utility and integration with the ElizaOS framework have been a subject of community discussion.

entities.name: DorianD
entities.description: A user involved in discussions about ElizaOS, token utility, and the challenges of integrating agent technology with decentralized networks.

entities.name: Shaw
entities.description: An individual who addressed concerns about AI16Z token utility by outlining future revenue-generating features for ElizaOS V2, including a hosted platform, payment layer, and API service wrapping.

entities.name: Bootstrap Plugin
entities.description: A plugin for ElizaOS v2 that is reported to have issues, specifically around a missing runtime.startRun() method.

entities.name: JIMMY
entities.description: An agent ecosystem token with unclear integration paths into the core ElizaOS platform.

entities.name: ELI5
entities.description: An agent ecosystem token with unclear integration paths into the core ElizaOS platform.

entities.name: DegenAI
entities.description: A token in the agent ecosystem that is reportedly bought back by the AutoFun fee system using AI16Z.

entities.name: Swarms
entities.description: A feature in ElizaOS V2 representing multi-agent teams designed to self-complete tasks.

entities.name: Dynamic Memory
entities.description: A feature in ElizaOS V2 that allows agents to recall user preferences.

entities.name: TEE
entities.description: Trusted Execution Environment, a feature in ElizaOS V2 offering enhanced security for transaction processing.

entities.name: CLI
entities.description: Command Line Interface for ElizaOS, featuring 34 plugins for one-line installation with TypeScript types in v2.

entities.name: RAG
entities.description: Retrieval-Augmented Generation capabilities included in ElizaOS v2, designed for instant retrieval with auto citations.

entities.name: Form Plugin
entities.description: A new plugin for ElizaOS that allows other plugins to build forms, enhancing user input handling and UI interactions.

entities.name: Agent-to-Agent (A2A) Marketplace
entities.description: A new concept within ElizaOS where agents will autonomously transact with one another, with AI16Z tokens planned as the settlement currency.

entities.name: AutoFun
entities.description: A platform or service whose fee system reportedly generates AI16Z tokens, which are then used to buy back DegenAI.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control and collaboration, mentioned in the context of ElizaOS deployment repositories.

entities.name: Coolify
entities.description: A deployment tool or platform that works with containerized applications, including ElizaOS using its default compose file.

entities.name: Mattermost
entities.description: A communication platform that can be integrated with ElizaOS deployments, specifically mentioned in the context of the elizify project.

entities.name: X (Twitter)
entities.description: A social media platform that was mentioned in the context of integration discussions and feature requests within ElizaOS.
